data.title: The Daily Diadem: Alexandra Georgievna’s Fringe Tiara
data.meta_description: Wikimedia Commons Grand Duchess Alexandra Georgievna of Russia, born Princess Alexandra of Greece and Denmark, wears a diamond fringe tiara backed by a fabric kokoshnik in an official court portrait, ca. 1890; the diamond fringe
data.text:
Wikimedia Commons

Grand Duchess Alexandra Georgievna of Russia, born Princess Alexandra of Greece and Denmark, wears a diamond fringe tiara backed by a fabric kokoshnik in an official court portrait, ca. 1890; the diamond fringe may be the same one that was later worn by her widower’s second wife, Princess Olga Paley, and which was confiscated by the government after the revolution
